    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Front Cover, Vibration Damper, and Gerotor Oil Pump - Installation - Gerotor
        Oil Pump
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Gerotor Oil Pump</title>
        <figure id="f3000636" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj13/j13026.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the gerotor oil pump cover</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Gerotor oil pump cover</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dowel pins (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Gerotor assembly</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate inner gear with lithium assembly grease and install on crankshaft. Lubricate outer
                gear with lithium assembly grease and mesh with inner gear rotor in oil pump housing. Wipe off excess
                assembly grease.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3000637" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj13/j13025.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Gerotor oil pump housing</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Gerotor oil pump cover retaining bolts, M6 x 25 (5)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Gerotor oil pump cover</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align dowel pins and install oil pump cover on front cover. Install five retaining bolts (M6
                x 25) to oil pump cover. Tighten bolts to the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_139.xml" xrefid="e30006b">Special Torque</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
